Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.06,0:22:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(270,238)\fs18}防滑鞋
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.10,0:25:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  主层到了\NHere you are, sir. Main level, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.68,0:25:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  回去的时候见\NRight. See you on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.39,0:25:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-再见  -再见\N- Bye. - Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.89,0:25:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.48,0:25:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-早上好  先生  -早\N- Good morning, sir. - Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.94,0:25:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很久没见你来了\NWe haven't seen you for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.48,0:25:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴再次见到你\NNice to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.43,0:25:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-旅途愉快吗  -非常愉快  谢谢\N- Did you have a pleasant flight? - Very nice, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.94,0:26:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太空站保安部的米勒先生好像要在这里见我\NI think Mr. Miller of Station Security is supposed to meet me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.03,0:26:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要我帮你联系他吗  -麻烦你了  他来了\N- Well, May I call him for you? - Would you, please? Here he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.08,0:26:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好  弗洛伊德博士  -你好  米勒  你还好吗\N- Hello, Dr. Floyd. - Hello, Miller. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.58,0:26:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-抱歉我迟到了  -没关系\N- Sorry I'm late. - That's quite all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.95,0:26:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你精神不错  -谢谢  很高兴你回来了\N- Gee, you're looking great.. - Thank you. It's nice to have you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.91,0:26:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,旅途顺利吗\NDid you have a good flight?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.83,0:26:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-非常顺利  -那就好\N- Very nice indeed. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.38,0:26:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们过去吧  -请用17号好吗\N- Well, shall we go through? - Would you please use number 17?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.38,0:26:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  特纳小姐\NThank you, Miss Turner.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.46,0:26:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谢谢  -这边请\N- Thank you. - This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.26,0:26:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(360,138)\fs14\frz-5}法语\N\N意大利语\N\N日语
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.26,0:26:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(140,100)\fs14\frz-5}英语\N\N荷兰语\N\N俄语
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.84,0:26:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(315,46)\fs16\frz17\fax-0.3\fry-6}美国移民局
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.64,0:26:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎使用声纹识别\NWelcome to Voiceprint Identification.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.31,0:26:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红灯亮起时\NWhen you see the red light go on,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.10,0:26:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请按顺序说出\Nplease state in the following order:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.56,0:26:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您的目的地  您的国籍以及您的全名\NYour destination, your nationality and your full name.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.02,0:26:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先姓后名  加上缩写\NSurname first, Christian name and initial.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.61,0:26:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,月球  美国人  弗洛伊德  海伍德·R\NMoon. American. Floyd, Heywood R.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.24,0:26:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  您通过了声纹识别\NThank you. You are cleared through Voiceprint Identification.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.71,0:26:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.01,0:27:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我有时间吃早餐吗  -我觉得应该没问题\N- Have I got time for breakfast? - I think we can manage that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.02,0:27:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(110,35)\fs12\frz-2\fax0\fry0\bord0\c&H000000&\shad0\b1\fad(1000,1000)}希尔顿空间站
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.26,0:27:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有多少时间\NHow long have I got?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.51,0:27:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的飞行一小时十分钟后开始\NYour flight leaves in an hour and 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.18,0:27:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实际上  \NAs a matter of fact, 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.74,0:27:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在地球之光厅为你预定了位子\NI've reserved a table for you in the Earthlight Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.76,0:27:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的  谢谢\NOh, fine. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.82,0:27:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已经七八个月没来过了  对吗\NIt's been seven or eight months since you were here, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.44,0:27:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想想  去年六月  没错  大概八个月\NLet's see. last June. Yeah, about eight months.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.69,0:27:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你进来的时候应该看到新区新建的工程了吧\NI suppose you saw the work on the new section as you came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.44,0:27:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-建造得很棒  是吧  -是的  还不错\N- Coming along great, huh? - Yeah, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.11,0:27:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等一下\NOh, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.52,0:27:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(316,85)\fs12\frz6\fax0\fry0\bord0\c&H000000&\shad0\b1\fad(500,1000)}豪生地球之光厅
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.32,0:27:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(191,93)\fs8\frz-8\fax0.1\fry20\bord0\c&Hdddddd&\shad0\b1\fad(500,500)\fscx110}影像电话
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.15,0:27:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得去打几个电话\NI've got to make a couple of phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.45,0:27:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先去餐厅  我一会儿去找你\NYou go on ahead in the restaurant. I'll meet you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.99,0:27:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.81,0:27:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(335,65)\fs16\frz8\fax-0.1\fry0\bord0\c&Hdddddd&\shad0\b1\fad(100,0)\fscx110}请拨号
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.73,0:27:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特拉维斯先生  请联系气象局\NWill Mr. Travers please contact the Met Office. 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.94,0:27:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特拉维斯先生  请联系气象局\NWill Mr. Travers please contact the Met office.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.85,0:27:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-爸爸  -你好\N- Dad? - Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.31,0:28:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好  -你好  小丫头\N- Hello. - Hi, squirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.02,0:28:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在做什么\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.11,0:28:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在玩\NPlaying.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.28,0:28:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈在哪\NWhere's Mummy?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.95,0:28:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去购物了\NGone to shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.70,0:28:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谁在照看你  -瑞秋\N- Who's taking care of you? - Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.37,0:28:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我能和瑞秋通话吗  -她去洗手间了\N- May I speak to Rachel, please? - She's gone to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.04,0:28:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你明天来参加我的派对吗\NAre you coming to my party tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.04,0:28:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  宝贝  我去不了\NI'm sorry, sweetheart, but I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.92,0:28:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不行\NWhy not?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.25,0:28:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为爸爸在旅行\NWell, you know, Daddy's traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.97,0:28:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常抱歉  但我真的来不了\NVery sorry about it, but I just can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.80,0:28:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过我会送你一份很棒的礼物\NI'm going to send you a very nice present, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.27,0:28:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.48,0:28:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你有什么想要的礼物吗  -有\N- Anything special that you want? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.89,0:28:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.27,0:28:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,电话\NA telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.36,0:28:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经有很多电话了\NWe've got lots of telephones already.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.73,0:28:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就没有其他想要的生日礼物吗\NCan't you think of anything else for your birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.03,0:28:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特别的礼物\NSomething very special?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.24,0:28:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有  -是什么\N- Yes. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.07,0:28:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婴猴\NA bush baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.37,0:28:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婴猴  我们看情况吧\NA bush baby? We'll have to see about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.08,0:28:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宝贝  我想让你给妈妈带个口信\NListen, sweetheart, I want you to tell Mummy something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.15,0:28:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能记住吗\NWill you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.12,0:29:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-能  -告诉妈妈我打过电话  好吗\N- Yeah. - Tell Mummy that I telephoned. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.91,0:29:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好  -明天我会再打个电话\N- Yeah. - And that I'll try to telephone again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.71,0:29:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能告诉她吗\NNow, will you tell her that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.59,0:29:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.55,0:29:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  宝贝  祝你明天生日快乐\NOkay, sweetheart. Have a nice birthday tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.76,0:29:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.01,0:29:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也祝你明天的生日派对能精彩有趣  好吗\NAnd have a nice birthday party tomorrow too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.81,0:29:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.06,0:29:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  保重  乖乖听话  好吗\NOkay. Now, take care and be a good girl, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.90,0:29:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  再见\NAll right. Bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.36,0:29:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见  生日快乐\NBye-bye. Happy birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.08,0:29:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(191,43)\fs18\frz0\fax0\bord0\c&Hffffee&\shad0\b1\fad(0,0)\fscx100\fnMicrosoft YaHei UI}收费\N1.70美元\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.89,0:29:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在等了多久了\NКоторым часы идёт?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.61,0:29:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约两小时了\NЭээ, приблизительно в два часа.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.32,0:29:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能去天文台了吗\NМожет быть, пойдем в обсерваторию
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.39,0:29:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等他来了我们就去\NКак только он придет
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.66,0:29:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埃琳娜  见到你真高兴\NElena, how nice to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.50,0:29:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海伍德  在这见到你真是个惊喜\NHeywood, what a wonderful surprise to meet you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.13,0:29:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你气色真好  -谢谢  你也很精神\N- You're looking wonderful. - Thank you. You're looking well too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.21,0:29:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位是我的好友  海伍德·弗洛伊德博士\NThis is my good friend, Dr. Heywood Floyd.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.47,0:29:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我想向你介绍卡丽南博士  -你好\N- I'd like you to meet Dr. Kalinan. - How do?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.97,0:29:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯特拉涅瓦博士\NDr. Stretyneva.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.19,0:29:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好  -你好\N- How do you do? - How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.14,0:29:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位是安德烈·斯梅斯洛夫博士\NAnd this is Dr. Andrei Smyslov.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.65,0:29:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-弗洛伊德  -你好  久仰大名\N- Floyd. - How do you do? I've heard a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.89,0:30:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请坐\NDo sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.77,0:30:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们...  -不  请坐\N- Well, we... - No, no, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.44,0:30:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.84,0:30:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要喝点什么吗  博士  -不用了  谢谢\N- Would you like a drink, doctor? - No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.99,0:30:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还没吃早餐\NI haven't had breakfast yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.25,0:30:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人在餐厅等我\NSomeone's meeting me in the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.43,0:30:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你们不介意  我就陪你们坐一会儿\NWell, if you don't mind, I'll just sit with you a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.33,0:30:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我就得走了\NThen I must be off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.23,0:30:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你确定吗  -确定  谢谢\N- Are you quite sure? - Quite sure, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.86,0:30:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-格雷戈近来好吗  -他很好\N- Well, how's Gregor? - He's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.35,0:30:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在波罗的海做水下研究\NHe's been doing some underwater research in the Baltic...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.11,0:30:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以恐怕我们最近没什么机会见面\Nso I'm afraid we don't get to see very much of each other these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.30,0:30:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-等你见到他的时候  代我向他问好  -当然\N- When you see him, give him my regards. - Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.04,0:30:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要去哪  上还是下\NWell, where are you all off to? Up or down?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.27,0:30:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要回家\NWe're going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.54,0:30:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们刚花了三个月时间\NWe've just spent three months
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.56,0:30:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在查林科基地调校新天线\Ncalibrating the new antenna at Tchalinko.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.67,0:30:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你呢  -我要去克拉维斯环形山\N- What about you? - I'm just on my way up to Clavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.31,0:30:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗\NOh, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.47,0:30:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗洛伊德博士  希望你不会嫌我刨根问底\NDr. Floyd, I hope you don't think I'm being too inquisitive...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.53,0:30:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许你可以跟我们说说\Nbut perhaps you can clear up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.40,0:30:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发生在那里的神秘事件\Nthe great big mystery about what has been going on up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.02,0:30:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕我不明白你的意思\NI'm afraid I don't know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.27,0:31:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过去的两周里\NWell, it's just that for the past, er, two weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.40,0:31:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在克拉维斯环形山发生了一些非常奇怪的事\Nsome extremely odd things have been happening at Clavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.27,0:31:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是吗  -是的\N- Really? - Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.26,0:31:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如  给基地打电话时\NWell, for one thing, whenever you phone the base,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.90,0:31:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只能听到一段录音\Nall you can get is a recording...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.40,0:31:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不断重复说着  电话线路暂时出现了故障\Nwhich repeats that the phone lines are temporarily out of order.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.57,0:31:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大概是设备出了故障\NProbably having some trouble with their equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.03,0:31:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者类似的情况\NOr something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.98,0:31:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.57,0:31:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  我们一开始也是这么认为的\NYes, that's what we thought was the explanation at first...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.60,0:31:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这种情况已经持续了十天\Nbut it's been going on now for the past 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.75,0:31:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过去十天里你们都联系不上任何人吗\NI mean, you haven't been able to contact anyone for the past 10 days?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.61,0:31:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.34,0:31:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明白了\NOh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.57,0:31:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有件事  海伍德\NThere's another thing, Heywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.03,0:31:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两天前  我们有一艘火箭巴士\NTwo days ago, one of our rocket buses...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.76,0:31:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想在克拉维斯环形山紧急降落  结果被拒绝了\Nwas denied permission for an emergency landing at Clavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.57,0:31:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这听起来确实很奇怪\NWell, that does sound odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.60,0:31:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  恐怕这会引发一些争端\NYes, yes. I'm afraid there's going to be a bit of a row about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.13,0:31:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拒绝人类降落\NDenying the men permission to land
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.70,0:31:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直接违反了国际宇航公约\Nis a direct violation of the IAS Convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.16,0:31:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  当然  当然\NYes. Of course. Of course. 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.10,0:31:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇航员们安全返回了吗\NDid the crew get back all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.24,0:31:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  他们很幸运\NYes. Fortunately, they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.75,0:31:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就好\NWell, I'm glad about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.39,0:32:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗洛伊德博士  虽然你可能\NDr. Floyd, at the risk of pressing you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.33,0:32:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不太愿意谈论这方面的事\Non a point you seem reticent to discuss...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.57,0:32:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我能问个直接的问题吗\Nmay I ask you a straightforward question?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.27,0:32:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然可以\NWell, certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.53,0:32:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说  我们收到可靠的消息称\NQuite frankly, we have had some very reliable intelligence reports...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.03,0:32:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克拉维斯环形山爆发了严重的传染病\Nthat quite a serious epidemic has broken out at Clavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.78,0:32:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,某种未知来源的传染病\NSomething, apparently, of an unknown origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.90,0:32:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请问这是事实吗\NIs this, in fact, what has happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.58,0:32:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  斯梅斯洛夫博士  但是\NI'm sorry, Dr. Smyslov, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.14,0:32:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我无权谈论这件事\NI'm really not at liberty to discuss this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.42,0:32:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以理解\NI understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.02,0:32:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这种传染病肯定很容易扩散到我们的基地\NBut this epidemic could quite easily spread to our base.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.47,0:32:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们理应知晓所有事实  弗洛伊德博士\NWe should be given all the facts, Dr. Floyd.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.81,0:32:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  我知道\NYes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.49,0:32:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说了  我无权谈论这件事\NAs I said, I'm not at liberty to discuss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.41,0:33:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你确定不一起喝一杯吗\NNow, are you sure you won't change your mind about that drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.48,0:33:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我确定  我真得走了\NNo, I'm positive. I really must be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.03,0:33:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你和你妻子\NWell, I hope that you and your wife
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.31,0:33:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能去参加六月份的国际宇航大会\Ncan come to the IAC Conference in June.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.35,0:33:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们尽量  希望能去\NWell, we gotta try. I hope we can make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.84,0:33:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是来的话\NIf you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.72,0:33:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,记得带上你那可爱的女儿一起\Nyou do remember to bring that darling little daughter with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.69,0:33:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那要看她学校放不放假之类的了\NThat'll all depend on school vacations and all that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.20,0:33:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果能去  肯定去\NBut if we can, we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.53,0:33:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别忘了  \NDon't forget 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.00,0:33:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你们去美国的话  我们热情欢迎你们的造访\Nyou've got a standing invitation if you ever get to the states.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.88,0:33:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然不会忘  格雷戈和我非常期望见到你们\NNo, of course not. Gregor and I will look forward to seeing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.73,0:33:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那再见了  埃琳娜\NWell, goodbye, Elena.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.73,0:33:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴见到你们大家\NIt's been a pleasure meeting you all. 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.76,0:33:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯梅斯洛夫博士\NDr. Smyslov.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.87,0:33:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管你去克拉维斯环形山的目的是什么  弗洛伊德博士\NWhatever the reasons for your visit to Clavius, Dr. Floyd,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.58,0:33:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝你好运\Nthe very best of luck to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.09,0:33:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.44,0:33:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女士们\NLadies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.72,0:33:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们现在肯定很艰难\NНаверное, им очень трудно
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.33,0:33:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然啊\NПо видимости
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.59,0:33:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  非常艰难\NДа, очень трудно
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.59,0:36:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(157,30)\b1\shad0\bord0\frz-2\fax0.1\fad(0,500)}零重力厕所\N{\fs13}旅客使用前请仔细阅读操作指南
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.88,0:40:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(252,240)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs18\fax0\fad(0,500)}安全
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.05,0:41:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思  哈沃森博士  我拍完了\NExcuse me, Dr. Halvorsen. I'm through now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.31,0:41:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-非常感谢  先生们  -不客气\N- Thank you very much, gentlemen. - You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.23,0:41:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么\NWell...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.87,0:41:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道大家都想和我一起\NI know you will all want to join with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.03,0:41:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎我们杰出的朋友和同事\Nin welcoming our distinguished friend and colleague...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.06,0:42:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来自国家航天委员会的海伍德·弗洛伊德博士\Nfrom the National Council of Astronautics, Dr. Heywood Floyd.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.62,0:42:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗洛伊德博士今天特地来到克拉维斯环形山\NDr. Floyd has come up specially to Clavius to be with us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.08,0:42:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在简报会开始之前\NAnd before the briefing,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.04,0:42:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道他想跟大家说几句\NI know he'd like to have a few words with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.43,0:42:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗洛伊德博士\NDr. Floyd?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.66,0:42:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  哈沃森博士\NThank you, Dr. Halvorsen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.82,0:42:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家好  很高兴再次见到各位\NHi, everybody. Nice to be back with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.92,0:42:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首先  霍威尔博士要我转达\NFirst of all, I bring a personal message from Dr. Howell...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.42,0:42:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他对你们深深的谢意\Nwho has asked me to convey his deepest appreciation to all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.83,0:42:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你们做出了诸多牺牲\Nfor the many sacrifices you've had to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.98,0:42:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然  也要祝贺你们的发现\NAnd, of course, his congratulations on your discovery...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.41,0:42:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那应该是科学史上\Nwhich may well prove to be among
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.39,0:42:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最重要的发现\Nthe most significant in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.31,0:42:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么\NNow...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.23,0:42:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道这段时间以来\NI know there have been
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.26,0:43:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出现了相冲突的两种观点\Nsome conflicting views held by some of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.41,0:43:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是否该采取完备的安全措施一事争执不休\Nregarding the need for complete security in this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.27,0:43:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更确切地说  是你们反对目前的掩饰性说法\NMore specifically, your opposition to the cover story...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.63,0:43:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让外界以为基地爆发了传染病\Ncreated to give the impression there's an epidemic at the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.06,0:43:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道  除了坚持原则之外\NI understand that beyond it being a matter of principle...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.50,0:43:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们还非常担心\Nmany of you are troubled by 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.57,0:43:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种传染病的说法\Nthe concern and anxiety this story of an epidemic
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.81,0:43:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能会让地球上的亲朋好友担惊受怕\Nmight cause to your relatives and friends on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.58,0:43:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我完全能理解你们的反对观点\NWell, I completely sympathize with your negative views.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.54,0:43:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我自己也觉得这个掩饰性说法很尴尬\NI find this cover story personally embarrassing, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.02,0:43:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过  我可以接受对这事绝对保密的必要性\NHowever, I accept the need for absolute secrecy in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.14,0:43:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你们也能接受\NAnd I hope you will too.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.61,0:43:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信各位肯定清楚\NI'm sure you're all aware of the extremely grave potential...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.75,0:43:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果未经充分准备\Nfor cultural shock and social disorientation...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.62,0:43:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不等适当的时机就贸然公布情况\Ncontained in this present situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.10,0:43:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么此事极有可能\Nif the facts were prematurely and suddenly made public
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.72,0:44:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引发强烈的文化冲击和社会动乱\Nwithout adequate preparation and conditioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.43,0:44:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总之  这是委员会的看法\NAnyway, this is the view of the Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.22,0:44:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我此行的目的\NThe purpose of my visit here
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.34,0:44:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是进一步收集情况和相关观点\Nis to gather additional facts and opinions on the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.81,0:44:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备一份报告交给委员会\Nand to prepare a report to the Council...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.94,0:44:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以供他们参考  何时  以何种方式\N...recommending when and how
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.67,0:44:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,公布这一消息\Nthe news should eventually be announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.54,0:44:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果各位想告诉我你们的看法\NIf any of you would like to give me your views and opinions...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.33,0:44:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也可以私下跟我说\Nin private, if you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.42,0:44:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我非常乐意把你的看法写进报告\NI'll be only too happy to include them in my report.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.28,0:44:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,差不多就这样吧\NWell, I think that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.04,0:44:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么问题吗\NAny questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.23,0:44:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗洛伊德博士  你知道\NDr. Floyd, have you any idea how much longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.60,0:44:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个掩饰性说法还要维持多久吗\Nthis cover story will have to be maintained?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.19,0:44:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道  比尔\NI don't know, Bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.13,0:44:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得只要委员会断定\NI suppose it'll be maintained
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.55,0:44:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有继续使用的必要  就会一直用下去\Nas long as deemed necessary by the Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.32,0:44:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了  必须有足够的时间\NAnd, of course, there must be adequate time 
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.71,0:44:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进行充分的研究\Nfor a full study to be made in situation
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.41,0:45:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才能考虑对外公开\Nbefore any thought can be given to making a public announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.20,0:45:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对了  有些人可能已经知道 \NOh yes, as some of you already know, 
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.46,0:45:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,委员会要求\Nthe Council has requested that 
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.06,0:45:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这件事的所有知情者\Nformal security oaths be obtained in writing...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.20,0:45:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都要手写一份正式的保密承诺\Nfrom everyone who has knowledge of this event.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.31,0:45:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有其他问题吗\NWere there any more questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.81,0:45:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信大家肯定都想\NI'm sure we'll all want to 
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.04,0:45:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全力配合弗洛伊德博士\Ncooperate with Dr. Floyd as fully as possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.45,0:45:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既然没有其他问题了\Nand as there seems to be no more questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.01,0:45:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该开始做简报了\NI think we ought to get on with the briefing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.01,0:45:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谢谢  弗洛伊德博士  -谢谢\N- Thank you, Dr. Floyd. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.08,0:47:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有谁饿了吗\NAnybody hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.23,0:47:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-太好了  -瞧瞧\N- Great. - Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.96,0:47:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-都有什么  -应有尽有\N- What do we got? - You name it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.49,0:47:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是鸡肉的吗  -算是吧\N- Is this chicken? - Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.58,0:47:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正都一个味道\NTastes the same, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.18,0:47:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有火腿的吗\NGot any ham?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.60,0:47:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火腿  火腿  火腿\NHam, ham, ham...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.28,0:47:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到了\NThere, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.31,0:47:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看着还挺不错的嘛\NLook pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.42,0:47:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,食品做得越来越好了\NThey're getting better at it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.32,0:47:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你刚刚那番讲话很精彩  海伍德\NYou know, that was an excellent speech you gave us, Heywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.33,0:47:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\NIt certainly was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.31,0:47:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯定大大提升了士气\NI'm sure it beefed up morale a hell of a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.64,0:47:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢了  拉尔夫\NThanks, Ralph.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.30,0:47:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便说一句  我觉得你们两个都做得很棒\NBy the way, I want to say that both of you've done a wonderful job.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.97,0:47:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很欣赏你们处理这件事的方法\NI appreciate the way you've handled this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.43,0:47:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我们看来\NWell, the way we look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.29,0:47:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,按你的意思行事  是我们的职责\Nit's our job to do this thing the way you want it done.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.53,0:47:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能效劳就很开心了\NWe're only too happy to be able to oblige.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.74,0:48:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看过这些照片吗\NHave you seen these yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.49,0:48:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是什么  能给我看看吗\NWhat are they? Can I have a look at them?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.87,0:48:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是这一切的源头\NHere's what started the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.65,0:48:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.68,0:48:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最开始发现时\NWhen we first found it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.29,0:48:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们以为这可能就是一块露出地面的磁铁石\Nwe thought it might be an outcrop of magnetic rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.06,0:48:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但所有的地质证据都与这一推测相悖\Nbut all the geological evidence was against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.41,0:48:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即便是一大块镍铁陨石\NAnd not even a big nickel-iron meteorite
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.96,0:48:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也无法产生如此强烈的磁场\Ncould produce a field as intense as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.36,0:48:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们决定去实地勘察\NSo we decided to have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.32,0:48:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们猜想这可能是某种埋入式结构的上层部分\NWe thought it might be the upper part of some buried structure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.75,0:48:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是进行了全面挖掘\Nso we excavated out on all sides,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.54,0:48:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但可惜的是  没有其他发现\Nbut unfortunately, we didn't find anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.87,0:48:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此外  几乎可以确定\NAnd what's more, the evidence seems pretty conclusive
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.43,0:48:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它的表面并没有自然侵蚀或外力作用的痕迹\Nthat it hasn't been covered up by natural erosion or other forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.08,0:48:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它似乎是被故意掩埋的\NIt seems to have been deliberately buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.70,0:48:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,故意掩埋\NDeliberately buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.66,0:48:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喝点咖啡怎么样\NWell, how about a little coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.17,0:48:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-太好了  -好主意\N- Great. - Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.57,0:48:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我猜你们应该完全不知道这是什么玩意儿吧\NI don't suppose you have any idea what the damn thing is, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.62,0:48:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们倒是想知道啊\NI wish to hell we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.21,0:48:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确实不知道  我们只能确定\NNo, the only thing we're sure of is that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.80,0:49:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它是在400万年前被掩埋的\Nit was buried 4 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.62,0:49:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我必须说 \NWell, I must say, 
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.99,0:49:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们还是有所发现的\Nyou guys have certainly come up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.45,0:49:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当心  很烫\NWatch this, now. It's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.60,0:54:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(192,40)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs25\fax0\fad(0,0)\c&HFFFFEE&}木星任务{\fs19} \N\N18个月后
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.61,0:58:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(330,80)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs15\fax0.1\frz-40)\c&HFF9600&}下次传输\N倒计时
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.19,0:58:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(330,80)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs15\fax0.1\frz-40)\c&HFFe600&\b1}BBC12台
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.64,0:58:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(330,80)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs15\fax0.1\frz-40)\c&HFFb600&\b1}今夜世界
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.60,0:58:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚上好\NGood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.99,0:58:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三周前  美国航天器"发现一号"\NThree weeks ago, the American spacecraft Discovery One
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.21,0:59:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开启了前往木星的5亿英里航程\Nleft on its half-billion-mile voyage to Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.24,0:59:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也是载人航天器首次尝试登陆这一遥远星球\NThis marked the first manned attempt to reach this distant planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.28,0:59:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天下午早些时候\NEarlier this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.48,0:59:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,《今日世界》录制了与发现号航天员的采访视频\NThe World Tonight recorded an interview with the crew of Discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.15,0:59:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们距离地球8000万英里\Nat a distance of 80 million miles from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.47,0:59:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们说的话需经过七分钟\NIt took seven minutes for our words
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.16,0:59:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才能传至这一巨型航天器\Nto reach the giant spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.19,0:59:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这种时间延迟已在视频中经过剪辑处理\Nbut this time delay has been edited from this recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.56,0:59:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我台记者马丁·艾莫采访了航天员\NOur reporter Martin Amer speaks to the crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.14,0:59:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现一号的航天员为五名男性\NThe crew of Discovery One consists of five men
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.49,0:59:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及最新一代的HAL 9000计算机\Nand one of the latest generation of the HAL 9000 computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.66,0:59:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五人中有三人以睡眠状态登舱\NThree of the five men were put aboard asleep
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.14,0:59:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更准确地说  是以休眠状态\Nor, to be more precise, in a state of hibernation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.59,0:59:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,分别为查尔斯·亨特博士  杰克·凯博尔博士\NThey were Dr. Charles Hunter, Dr. Jack Kimball
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.66,0:59:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及维克多·卡明斯基博士\Nand Dr. Victor Kaminsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.02,0:59:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们采访到了任务指令长大卫·鲍曼博士\NWe spoke with mission commander Dr. David Bowman
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.94,0:59:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和他的副手弗兰克·普尔博士\Nand his deputy, Dr. Frank Poole.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.45,0:59:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下午好  先生们  一切都好吗\NWell, good afternoon, gentlemen. How is everything going?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.52,0:59:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好极了\NMarvelous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.76,0:59:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没什么...\NHave no...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.38,0:59:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没什么可抱怨的\NWe have no complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.32,0:59:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听你们这么说可真是太好了\NWell, I'm very glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.04,1:00:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也相信全世界都会和我一起\NAnd I'm sure that the entire world would join me
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.75,1:00:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝愿你们此次远航能够安全和成功\Nin wishing you a safe and successful voyage.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.46,1:00:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-非常感谢  -谢谢你\N- Thanks very much. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.57,1:00:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管在此前的太空探索活动中已经使用过休眠方式\NAlthough hibernation has been used on previous space efforts,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.67,1:00:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这是首次\Nthis is the first time that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.80,1:00:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇航员在出发前就进入了休眠状态\Nmen have been put into hibernation before departure.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.17,1:00:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何这样安排\NWhy was this done?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.98,1:00:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样安排是为了最大限度地储存\NWell, this was done in order to achieve the maximum conservation
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.51,1:00:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的生命维持资源  主要是食物和空气\Nof our life-support capabilities, basically food and air.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.20,1:00:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正在休眠的三名航天员属于调查小组\NNow the three hibernating crew members represent the survey team.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.80,1:00:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(182,63)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs15\fax0\frz222\c&H000000&\b1}卡明斯基博士
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.12,1:00:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们临近木星时\NAnd their efforts won't be utilized
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.00,1:00:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们才会派上用场\Nuntil we're approaching Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.10,1:00:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普尔博士  处于休眠状态是怎么感觉\NDr. Poole, what's it like while you're in hibernation?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.00,1:00:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就跟睡觉一样\NIt's exactly like being asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.69,1:00:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全不会感觉到时间的流逝\NYou have absolutely no sense of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.77,1:00:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一的区别是不会做梦\NThe only difference is that you don't dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.42,1:00:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据我了解  那种状态下每分钟只会呼吸一次\NAs I understand it, you only breathe once a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.21,1:00:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是真的吗\NIs this true?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.88,1:00:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错  而且每分钟的心跳只有三次\NWell, that's right, and the heart beats three times a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.54,1:00:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\pos(22,68)\b1\shad0\bord0\fs14\c&HFFFFFF&\b1}心脑血管\N\N\N代谢水平\N\N\N{\fscx70\fsp-1}中枢神经系统\N\N\N{\fscx100\fsp3}肺功能\N\N\N{\fsp0}系统综合\N\N\N运动系统
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.46,1:00:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,体温一般会降至3℃左右\NBody temperature is usually down to about three degrees centigrade.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.68,1:00:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现号的第六名航天员不用担心\NThe sixth member of the Discovery crew was not concerned
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.38,1:01:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,休眠的问题\Nabout the problems of hibernation,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.52,1:01:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他是最新机器智能的结晶\Nfor he was the latest result in machine intelligence:
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.20,1:01:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HAL 9000计算机  它可以「复制」...\NThe HAL 9000 computer, which can reproduce,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.00,1:01:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过有些专家更喜欢称之为「模仿」\Nthough some experts still prefer to use the word "mimic",
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.11,1:01:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...人类大脑中的大多数活动\Nmost of the activities of the human brain
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.58,1:01:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且其运行速度和可靠性不可估量\Nand with incalculably greater speed and reliability.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.92,1:01:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们接下来采访了HAL 9000计算机\NWe next spoke with the HAL 9000 computer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.73,1:01:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们得知  它也被称作哈尔\Nwhom, we learned, one addresses as "Hal."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.35,1:01:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下午好  哈尔  一切都好吗\NGood afternoon, Hal. How's everything going?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.87,1:01:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下午好  艾莫先生  一切都十分顺利\NGood afternoon, Mr. Amer. Everything is going extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.97,1:01:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈尔  此次任务你责任重大\NHal, you have an enormous responsibility on this mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.96,1:01:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从很多方面来说\NIn many ways 
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.58,1:01:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你身上的担子或许是这次任务中最重的\Nperhaps the greatest responsibility of any single mission element.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.70,1:01:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是飞船的大脑以及中枢神经系统\NYou're the brain and central nervous system of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.74,1:01:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的职责包括\NAnd your responsibilities include
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.27,1:01:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看护休眠中的航天员\Nwatching over the men in hibernation.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.68,1:01:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这会让你缺乏自信心吗\NDoes this ever cause you any lack of confidence?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.94,1:01:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这么说吧  艾莫先生\NLet me put it this way, Mr. Amer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.59,1:01:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9000系列是有史以来最可靠的计算机\NThe 9000 Series is the most reliable computer ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.59,1:02:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9000系列计算机\NNo 9000 computer
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.13,1:02:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从未犯过错误  也从未歪曲过信息\Nhas ever made a mistake or distorted information.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.07,1:02:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论如何形容定义  我们都是\NWe are all, by any practical definition of the words,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.63,1:02:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万无一失  不会出错的\Nfoolproof and incapable of error.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.20,1:02:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈尔  尽管你具备高度智能\NHal, despite your enormous intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.95,1:02:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你曾因为需要依靠人类来执行操作\Nare you ever frustrated by your dependence on people
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.18,1:02:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而懊恼过吗\Nto carry out actions?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.53,1:02:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全没有\NNot in the slightest bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.06,1:02:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢与人类共事\NI enjoy working with people.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.37,1:02:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我与普尔博士和鲍曼博士保持着高度活跃的关系\NI have a stimulating relationship with Dr. Poole and Dr. Bowman.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.05,1:02:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的任务职责\NMy mission responsibilities
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.63,1:02:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,囊括了飞船所有的运行操作\Nrange over the entire operation of the ship
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.85,1:02:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我一直忙得不可开交\Nso I am constantly occupied.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.93,1:02:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也在尽我所能\NI am putting myself to the fullest possible use
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.63,1:02:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想这对任何一个有意识的实体来说\Nwhich is all, I think, that any conscious entity
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.16,1:02:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是梦寐以求的\Ncan ever hope to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.08,1:02:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普尔博士  在这将近一年的时间里\NDr. Poole, what's it like living for the better part of a year
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.58,1:02:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直与哈尔近距离接触是什么感觉\Nin such close proximity with Hal?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.29,1:02:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟你之前对他的描述差不多\NWell, it's pretty close to what you said about him earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.73,1:02:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就像是第六名航天员\NHe's just like a sixth member of the crew...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.02,1:02:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很快就习惯了他会说话的事实\Nvery quickly get adjusted to the idea that he talks,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.68,1:03:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会把他当作一个人来看待\Nand you think of him really just as another person.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.42,1:03:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在与计算机交流的过程中\NIn talking to the computer,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.92,1:03:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人感觉到他能做出情绪反应\None gets the sense that he's capable of emotional responses.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.90,1:03:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如  当我问到他的能力时\NFor example, when I asked him about his abilities,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.34,1:03:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他回答说自己是精准完美的\NI sensed a certain pride in his answer
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.19,1:03:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从中感到了一丝得意\Nabout his accuracy and perfection.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.67,1:03:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为哈尔具有真情实感吗\NDo you believe that Hal has genuine emotions?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.78,1:03:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他表现得像是有真情实感\NWell, he acts like he has genuine emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.95,1:03:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了  他的程序是这么设定的\NOf course, he's programmed that way
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.12,1:03:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让我们能更加方便地与他交流\Nto make it easier for us to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.78,1:03:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是至于他有没有感情\NBut as to whether or not he has real feelings
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.22,1:03:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得没有人能给出确切的答案\Nis something I don't think anyone can truthfully answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.22,1:03:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打扰一下  弗兰克\NExcuse me, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.43,1:04:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了  哈尔\NWhat is it, Hal?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.68,1:04:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们收到了你父母传来的消息\NWe've got the transmission from your parents coming in.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.95,1:04:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.56,1:04:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在这播放吧  把我移过去一点\NPut it on here, please. Take me in a bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.14,1:04:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NCertainly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.75,1:04:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好  弗兰克  -生日快乐  亲爱的\N- Hello, Frank. - Happy birthday, darling.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.41,1:04:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生日快乐  年年有今日  岁岁有今朝\NHappy birthday. Many happy returns of the day..
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.79,1:04:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-再升高一点  哈尔  -很高兴听到你和大卫都很好\N- A bit higher, Hal. - Glad to hear you and Dave are well.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.49,1:04:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你妈妈和我也都很好\NMother and I are both feeling wonderful too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.82,1:04:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷和莎莉本来也准备来跟你通话的\NRay and Sally were going to be here too
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.53,1:04:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但雷的背伤突然又犯了\Nbut at the last minute Ray's back went bad on him again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.58,1:04:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你喜欢这个蛋糕吗  -看起来很棒吧\N- How do you like your cake, dear? - Looks great, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.94,1:04:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜你不能和我们一起共享\NSorry you can't join us.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.73,1:04:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前几天我遇到了鲍勃\NI ran into Bob the other day.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.49,1:04:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说一定要让我代为祝你生日快乐\NHe said be sure to wish you happy birthday.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.58,1:04:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的全体学生也让我务必向你问好\NAll my students made me promise to send their best wishes too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.47,1:04:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在教室里总是谈到你  弗兰克\NYou know they talk about you all the time in the classroom, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.64,1:04:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你成了二年级学生心中的大名人了\NYou're a big celebrity in the second grade.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.70,1:04:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上周我们上了电视\NYou know we were on television last week.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.42,1:04:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错  你妈妈和我还有大卫的父母\NOh yes, yes. Your mother and I and Dave's parents 
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.84,1:04:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被问到我们如何看待自己的杰出的儿子\Nwere interviewed about what we thought of our illustrious sons.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.83,1:05:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以想象得出我们是怎么回答的\NHeh, you can imagine what we told them.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.77,1:05:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好像节目下周四就会播出\NI think it's being broadcast next Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.48,1:05:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许你能收听到\NPerhaps you'll be able to listen in.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.25,1:05:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对了  埃琳娜和比尔的事  我们也很激动\NOh, we were thrilled about Elaine and Bill, dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.27,1:05:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很乐意帮你给他们买礼物\NI'll be glad to get the present for you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.84,1:05:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过请告诉我预算是多少\Nbut please tell me how much I can spend.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.22,1:05:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对了  弗兰克  你的AGS19薪水\NOh, yes, Frank, about your AGS-19 payments...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.39,1:05:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我应该都帮你处理好了\NI think I straightened it out for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.16,1:05:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我昨天跟休斯顿那边的财务室谈过了\NI talked to the accounting office in Houston yesterday 
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.33,1:05:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们说下个月你应该就能收到\Nand they said you should be receiving
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.89,1:05:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,涨过之后的工资了\Nyour higher rates of pay by next month.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.38,1:05:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  弗兰克  我没什么要说的了\NWell, Frank, I can't think of anything else to say, now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.82,1:05:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,代我们向大卫问好\NGive our love to Dave.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.71,1:05:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错  记得问好\NOh yes. Be sure to give him our best regards.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.14,1:05:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们衷心地祝你生日快乐\NWe wish you the very happiest of birthdays.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.47,1:05:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝保佑\NGod bless!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.54,1:05:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切顺利  儿子\NAll the best, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.50,1:05:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs14\i1}♪祝你生日快乐♪\N{\rEng\fs10\i1}♪Happy birthday to you♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.80,1:05:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs14\i1}♪祝你生日快乐♪\N{\rEng\fs10\i1}♪Happy birthday to you♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.22,1:05:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs14\i1}♪祝你生日快乐  亲爱的弗兰克♪\N{\rEng\fs10\i1}♪Happy birthday, dear Frank♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.98,1:05:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs14\i1}♪祝你生日快乐♪\N{\rEng\fs10\i1}♪Happy birthday to you.♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.34,1:05:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下周三见\NSee you next Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.47,1:05:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝你生日快乐  弗兰克\NHappy birthday, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.23,1:05:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你  哈尔  请放平一点\NThank you, Hal. A bit flatter, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.70,1:06:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总之  后吃兵\NAnyway, queen takes pawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.49,1:06:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,象吃兵\NBishop takes knight's pawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.53,1:06:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这步棋下得漂亮\NLovely move.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.43,1:06:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车走一步到王\NRook to king one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.11,1:06:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思  弗兰克  我觉得你输了\NI'm sorry, Frank. I think you missed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.71,1:06:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后进三到象  象吃后\NQueen to bishop three. Bishop takes queen.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.43,1:06:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马吃象  朋友\NKnight takes bishop. Mate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.26,1:06:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错  你说得很对  我投降\NEr, yeah. Looks like you're right. I resign.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.63,1:06:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你  这盘棋下得很愉快\NThank you for a very enjoyable game.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.79,1:06:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  谢谢你\NYeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.93,1:07:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-晚上好  大卫  -你还好吗  哈尔\N- Good evening, Dave. - How are you, Hal?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.97,1:07:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-一切顺利  你呢  -还不错\N- Everything's running smoothly. And you? - Not too bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.51,1:07:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你又忙了一些工作上的事吗 \NHave you been doing more work? 
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.41,1:07:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,画了几幅草图\NA few sketches.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.52,1:07:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-可以给我看看吗  -当然\N- May I see them? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.03,1:07:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,画得真不错  大卫\NThat's a very nice rendering, Dave.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.33,1:07:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得你进步很大\NI think you've improved a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.98,1:07:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你能拿近点吗  -好\N- Can you hold it a bit closer? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.22,1:08:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是亨特博士吗\NThat's Dr. Hunter, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.37,1:08:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便问下\NBy the way...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.69,1:08:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你介意我问你个私人问题吗\Ndo you mind if I ask you a personal question?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.29,1:08:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  不介意\NNo, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.05,1:08:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请原谅我这么喜欢打听\NWell, forgive me for being so inquisitive...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.63,1:08:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但过去几周我一直都在想\Nbut during the past few weeks I've wondered...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.86,1:08:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对此次任务是否有了些疑虑\Nwhether you might be having second thoughts about the mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.01,1:08:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思\NHow do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.75,1:08:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真要说起来  很难定义\NWell, it's rather difficult to define.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.82,1:08:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许我只是在表达我对这件事的担忧\NPerhaps I'm just projecting my own concern about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.62,1:08:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道我从未打消过这样的疑虑\NI know I've never completely freed myself of the suspicion...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.14,1:08:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次任务存在一些非常奇怪的情况\Nthat there are some extremely odd things about this mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.26,1:08:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信你也同意我的话有一定的道理\NI'm sure you'll agree there's some truth in what I say.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.62,1:08:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也说不清  这是个很难回答的问题\NWell, I don't know. That's rather a difficult question to answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.13,1:08:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不介意谈谈这事吧  大卫\NYou don't mind talking about it, do you, Dave?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.55,1:08:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  不介意\NNo, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.44,1:09:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然没人会不知晓\NCertainly no one could have been unaware of 
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.59,1:09:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们出发前身边流传的离奇故事\Nthe very strange stories floating around before we left.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.48,1:09:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有传言说月球上挖出了一个东西\NRumors about something being dug up on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.22,1:09:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从没相信过这些传言\NI never gave these stories much credence...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.79,1:09:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但就某些已经发生的事来看\Nbut particularly in view of some other things that have happened
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.09,1:09:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很难不去想\NI find them difficult to put out of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.55,1:09:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如\NFor instance...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.21,1:09:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的准备工作是严格保密的\Nthe way all our preparations were kept under such tight security.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.23,1:09:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,且戏剧性地\NAnd the melodramatic touch of 
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.83,1:09:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让亨特博士  凯博尔博士  卡明斯基博士\Nputting Dr. Hunter, Kimball, and Kaminsky aboard
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.00,1:09:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以休眠状态登船\Nalready in hibernation,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.46,1:09:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,且他们各自单独训练了四个月之久\Nafter four months of training on their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.70,1:09:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这是要写宇航员心理状态报告吗\NYou working up your crew psychology report?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.81,1:09:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然\NOf course I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.64,1:09:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很抱歉  我知道这有点可笑\NSorry about this. I know it's a bit silly.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.13,1:09:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,稍等\NJust a moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.14,1:09:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,稍等\NJust a moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.89,1:09:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚在AE-35部件中发现一项故障\NI've just picked up a fault in the AE-35 unit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.94,1:10:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它将在72小时内完全丧失功能\NIt's going to go 100-percent failure within 72 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.40,1:10:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-现在还在操作范围内吗  -是的\N- Is it still within operational limits right now? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.50,1:10:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在彻底丧失功能前  它将一直保持运行\NAnd it will stay that way until it fails.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.12,1:10:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以说在彻底丧失功能前  我们还有72小时吗\NWould you say we have a reliable seventy-two hours to failure?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.46,1:10:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  这个数字十分准确\NYes. That's a completely reliable figure.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.24,1:10:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那看来我们只能把它换下来修理了\NWell, then I suppose we'll have to bring it in
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.27,1:10:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但首先我要和弗兰克商量一下\Nbut first I'd like to go over this with Frank
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.84,1:10:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后联络任务控制中心\Nand get on to Mission Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.90,1:10:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请把资料复印一份给我\NLet me have the hard copy on it, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.89,1:11:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XRD1号  这里是任务控制中心\NX-ray delta one, this is Mission Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.83,1:11:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们的2013号讯息已收到\NRoger your two-zero-one-three.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.81,1:11:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉你们遇到了一点麻烦\NSorry you fellows are having a bit of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.49,1:12:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们正在任务模拟器上查看遥测信息 \NWe're reviewing telemetric information in our mission simulator
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.70,1:12:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,稍后会给出建议\Nand will advise.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.93,1:12:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经收到你们要去舱外\NRoger your plan to go EVA
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.88,1:12:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在AE-35部件丧失功能前对其进行更换的计划\Nand replace alpha-echo-three-five unit prior to failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.07,1:12:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备好B飞行舱去舱外  哈尔\NPrepare B-pod for EVA, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.76,1:13:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开舱门  哈尔\NOpen the pod doors, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.33,1:19:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈尔  见鬼了  我没发现任何异常\NWell, Hal. I'm damned if I can find anything wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.87,1:20:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.09,1:20:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真令人费解\NIt's puzzling.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.75,1:20:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我之前从没见过这种情况\NI don't think I've ever seen anything quite like this before.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.23,1:20:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我建议\NI would recommend
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.48,1:20:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将部件放回去继续使用  直至其丧失功能\Nthat we put the unit back in operation and let it fail.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.41,1:20:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时候追查原因就简单了\NIt should then be a simple matter to track down the cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.39,1:20:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以接受  在进行替换时  \NWe can certainly afford to be out of communication...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.83,1:20:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通讯会有短时间的断开\Nfor the short time it will take to replace it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.78,1:20:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XRD1号  这里是任务控制中心\NX-ray delta one, this is Mission Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.62,1:20:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们的1930号讯息已收到\NRoger your one-niner-three-zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.57,1:20:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们同意你们更换一号部件\NWe concur with your plan to replace number-one unit...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.29,1:20:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以检查故障预报\Nto check fault prediction.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.28,1:20:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须告诉你们  我们的初步调查结果表明\NWe should advise you that our preliminary findings indicate 
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.44,1:20:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,飞船上的9000号计算机\Nthat your onboard 9000 computer
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.14,1:20:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,故障预测出错\Nis in error predicting the fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.42,1:21:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重复一遍  故障预测出错\NI say again, in error predicting the fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.72,1:21:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明白这听起来不大可能\NI know this sounds rather incredible,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.37,1:21:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但此结论基于\Nbut this conclusion is based on...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.36,1:21:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双子9000计算机的计算结果\Nthe results from our twin 9000 computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.02,1:21:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们自身也尚存疑虑\NWe're skeptical ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.37,1:21:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们正在运行交叉检验程序\Nand we're running cross-checking routines
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.67,1:21:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以判断此结论的可靠性\Nto determine reliability of this conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.43,1:21:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很抱歉出现了这种小故障  各位\NSorry about this little snag, fellows.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.52,1:21:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,调查完毕后  我们会立即通知你们\NWe'll get this info to you as soon as we work it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.41,1:21:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XRD1号  这里是任务控制中心\NX-ray delta one, this is Mission Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.20,1:21:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2049号  传送完毕\NTwo-zero-four-nine. Transmission concluded.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.42,1:21:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望你们不要担心这事\NI hope the two of you are not concerned about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.04,1:21:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不担心  哈尔\NNo, I'm not, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.69,1:21:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你确定吗\NAre you quite sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.52,1:21:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-确定  不过我想问你一个问题  -请问\N- Yeah. I'd like to ask you a question though. - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.39,1:21:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你如何解释你和双子9000间\NHow do you account for the discrepancy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.31,1:21:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,计算结果的差异\Nbetween you and the twin 9000?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.28,1:21:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为不存在问题\NWell, I don't think there is any question about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.19,1:21:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,差异只可能由人为错误造成\NIt can only be attributable to human error.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.70,1:21:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,类似问题此前也曾出现过\NThis sort of thing has cropped up before...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.81,1:22:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直都是因为人为错误\Nand it has always been due to human error.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.72,1:22:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着  哈尔\NListen, Hal...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.64,1:22:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在9000系列计算机中\Nthere's never been any instance at all of a...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.25,1:22:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否从未出现过计算失误的前例\Ncomputer error occurring in a 9000 Series, has there?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.61,1:22:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从未出现过  弗兰克\NNone whatsoever, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.50,1:22:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9000系列的运行记录完美无瑕\NThe 9000 Series has a perfect operational record.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.43,1:22:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我当然知道9000系列计算机的辉煌成就\NWell, of course I know the wonderful achievements of the 9000 Series,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.88,1:22:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是...\Nbut...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.99,1:22:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你确定计算机从未出过错吗\NAre you certain there's never been any case of even the most
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.85,1:22:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪怕是毫不起眼的小错误\Ninsignificant computer error?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.21,1:22:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从未出现过  弗兰克\NNone whatsoever, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.52,1:22:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说真的  你们不必对此担心\NQuite honestly, I wouldn't worry myself about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.75,1:22:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信你说得对  哈尔\NWell, I'm sure you're right, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.36,1:22:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的  非常感谢\NFine. Thanks very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.00,1:22:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克  我C号飞行舱的通讯器出了点问题\NOh, Frank, I'm having trouble with my transmitter in C-pod.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.87,1:22:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能和我过去看一眼吗\NWould you come down and take a look at it with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.62,1:22:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好  -待会儿见  哈尔\N- Sure. - See you later, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.31,1:23:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请旋转C舱  哈尔\NRotate C-pod, please, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.91,1:23:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出了什么问题  大卫\NWhat sort of trouble have you been having Dave?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.29,1:23:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的D频总有干扰\NI've been getting some interference in D-channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.15,1:23:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们来看看吧\NWe'll have a look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.97,1:23:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开舱门  哈尔\NOpen the door, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.99,1:24:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(500,50)\bord0\shad0\fs18\pos(195,35)\c&H100050&\b1}当心\N爆炸螺栓
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.50,1:24:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请旋转舱体  哈尔\NRotate pod, please, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.64,1:24:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,停止旋转  哈尔\NStop pod rotation, please, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.16,1:24:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请旋转舱体  哈尔\NRotate the pod, please, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.05,1:24:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请旋转舱体  哈尔\NRotate the pod, please, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.26,1:24:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他应该听不见我们说话了\NI don't think he can hear us.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.10,1:24:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请旋转舱体  哈尔\NRotate the pod, please, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.79,1:24:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  这样应该没问题了\NYeah, I'm sure we're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.08,1:24:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是什么想法\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.95,1:24:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定  你呢\NI'm not sure. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.70,1:24:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对他有种不好的预感\NI've got a bad feeling about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.75,1:24:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是吗  -是的  我确定\N- You do? - Yeah. Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.30,1:24:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不觉得吗\NDon't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.83,1:25:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也说不清  好像是\NI don't know. I think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.39,1:25:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然  他确实说得没错  \NYou know, of course though he's right about 
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.63,1:25:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9000系列计算机有着完美的运行记录\Nthe 9000 series having a perfect operational record.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.78,1:25:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确实如此\NThey do.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.90,1:25:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不幸的是  那听起来有点像出名的临终遗言\NUnfortunately, that sounds a little like famous last words.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.74,1:25:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  不过进行故障模式分析\NYeah. Still, it was his idea to carry out
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.07,1:25:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是他的主意  不是吗\Nthe failure mode analysis, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.47,1:25:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一点的确能彰显他的诚实与自信\NIt should certainly indicate his integrity and self-confidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.14,1:25:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他错了  这样就能确定无疑地证明\NIf he were wrong, it'd be the surest way of proving it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.17,1:25:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前提是他知道自己错了\NIt would be if he knew he was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.06,1:25:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫  我无法完全确定\NLook Dave, I can't put my finger on it,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.35,1:25:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我总觉得他有些古怪\Nbut I sense something strange about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.46,1:25:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我还是想不出一个合理的理由\NStill I can't think of a good reason 
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.69,1:25:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不将一号部件放回去\Nnot to put back the number one unit
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.83,1:25:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并继续执行故障模式分析\Nand carry on with the failure mode analysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.46,1:25:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  这点我同意\NNo, no, I agree about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.75,1:25:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就这么办吧\NWell let's get on with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.43,1:25:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的  但是  大卫\NOkay. But, look, Dave.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.72,1:25:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们把部件装回去  但它并没有丧失功能\NLet's say we put the unit back and it doesn't fail.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.62,1:25:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那在哈尔看来  就没有任何问题 \NThat would pretty well wrap it up 
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.49,1:25:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会查下去了  对吧\Nas far as Hal is concerned, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.45,1:25:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时我们的麻烦可就大了 \NWell, we'd be in very serious trouble. 
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.08,1:25:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  可不是嘛\NWe would, wouldn't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.22,1:25:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我们能怎么办\NWhat the hell can we do?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.91,1:26:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的选择很有限\NWell, we wouldn't have too many alternatives.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.61,1:26:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我看来  我们根本别无选择\NI don't think we'd have any alternatives.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.71,1:26:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这艘飞船的方方面面\NThere isn't a single aspect of ship operations
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.72,1:26:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都在他的掌控之下\Nthat's not under his control.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.25,1:26:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果事实证明他出了故障...\NIf he were proving to be malfunctioning...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.61,1:26:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们唯一的选择  就是断开计算机的连接\NI don't see we'd have any choice but disconnection.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.52,1:26:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕我的看法和你一致\NI'm afraid I agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.27,1:26:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别无他法了\NThere'd be nothing else to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.80,1:26:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这事有点棘手  -是啊\N- It'd be a bit tricky. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.03,1:26:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们得切断他的高级大脑功能\NWe'd have to cut his higher brain functions...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.89,1:26:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同时不能干扰到全自动化系统和监管系统\Nwithout disturbing the purely automatic and regulatory systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.80,1:26:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还得想办法将控制权转移给\NAnd we'd have to work out the transfer procedures
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.69,1:26:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地面计算机系统  从而继续执行任务\Nof continuing the mission under ground-based computer control.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.07,1:26:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 \NYeah. 
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.87,1:26:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那也比让哈尔继续管控安全得多\NWell, that's far safer than allowing Hal to continue running things.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.33,1:26:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我突然又想起来一件事\NYou know, another thing just occurred to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.86,1:26:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据我所知  9000计算机还从未被断开连接过\NAs far as I know, no 9000 computer has ever been disconnected.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.77,1:26:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9000计算机也从没出过问题\NNo 9000 computer has ever fouled up before.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.92,1:26:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是这个意思\NThat's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.61,1:27:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道他会对此有什么想法\NI'm not so sure what he'd think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.79,1:27:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(1000,2500)\bord0\shad0\fs28\pos(192,95)}中场休息
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.22,1:33:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备好G飞行舱去舱外  哈尔\NPrepare G-pod for EVA, Hal.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.31,1:33:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有他的无线电消息吗\NAny radio contact with him yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.94,1:33:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无线电仍无消息\NThe radio is still dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.90,1:33:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-能否追踪到他的行动轨迹  -是的  可以追踪到\N- Do you have a positive track on him? - Yes, I have a good track.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.11,1:33:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道出了什么问题吗\NDo you know what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.82,1:33:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  大卫  我没有足够的信息\NI'm sorry, Dave. I don't have enough information.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.78,1:33:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开舱门  哈尔\NOpen the pod door, Hal.
